Bookmakers can open if work protocols are in place and health guidance is followed.
Reduced capacity due to social distancing requirements and additional cleaning service.
Swimming pools may open with reduced capacity due to social distancing requirements and additional cleaning requirements.
Pubs and bars may open if they trade as a restaurant (a substantial meal must be provided). Reduced capacity is mandated.
Pubs and bars may open. Reduced capacity is mandated.
Theatres and music venues may open if they adhere to social distancing protocols and limit attendences to 50 persons.
Cinemas may open if they adhere to social distancing protocols and limit attendences to 50 persons.
Nighclubs are closed until further notice.
Places of worship may open but must restrict their numbers to less than 50 people inside.

source_url: Sports and leisure facilities may open but must restrict their numbers to less than 50 people inside.

details: Public transport is operating at reduced capacity and should only be used for essential journeys. Mask are mandatory as of 29 June 2020.
Hairdressers, barbers, nail and brow salons, beauty salons, spas, make-up application services, tanning, tattooing and piercing services may open. Guidelines must be followed.
Driving schools may re-open from 29 June 2020.
Wellbeing services (chiropractic, massage therapy, acupuncture, reflexology, homoeopathy) may re-open from 29 June 2020.
Adult education facilities may reopen from 29 June 2020.
All primary and secondary schools are closed indefinitely as of 13 March 2020.
Childcare facilities may reopen from 29 June 2020.
Playgrounds may reopen from 08 June 2020 with social distancing and cleaning in place.
Libraries may reopen from 08 June 2020 with social distancing and cleaning in place.
Tracks and stadiums for horse racing and greyhound racing may operate behind closed doors from 08 June 2020.
Casinos are closed from 27 March 2020 until 20 July 2020.
